Thu Mar 14 15:47:47 2002 <jdovc@te13.hq.eso.org>  abeans version: 1.22 
Wed Mar 13 11:05:56 2002  Gianluca Chiozzi  <gchiozzi@te4.hq.eso.org>

	* src/Makefile: 
	Added making and installing endorsed jar files

	* src/abeansStart: 
	Added handling of endorsed directory path.
	This is necessary to allow overriding packages that are part of
	the JDK endorsed standards.
        See
           http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4/docs/guide/standards/index.html
        and
           http://groups.google.de/groups?q=endorsed.dirs&hl=de&selm=3C6FED66.7010404%40tkuhn.de&rnum=2
        for details
        In order not to patch the JDK installation, we create our own
	endorsed directory(ies) and tell explicitly 
        java and javac to look there using the 
	     -Djava.endorsed.dirs 
	system property.

	Added handling of $JAVA_OPTIONS environment variable.
	This can be used to pass specivic options and properties to the
	java command.

